{title: New Cut Road}
{artist: Bobby Bare}
{composer: written by Guy Clark}

I’m gonna [G]play it all night down a new cut road

Now Coalman’s Daddy said what’s it all coming to
Young [D7]people these days are just stubborn as mules
He can’t make um go he’s too old for that
It’s that [G]damned ole fiddle and that bowler hat

Now Coalman’s momma said let the boy stay
Cuz he’s [D7]raised up solid he can find his own way
But as for me honey I’m with you
Well I [G]always thought Kentucky was just passing through

Coalman’s little sister she started in a cry
And her [D7]daddy shook his head for the very last time
Coalman’s momma said somebody gotta do it
Wouldn’t [G]be no Kentucky less you didn’t stick to it Coalman

Coalman Bonner stood on the porch of that cabin
Watched um [D7]all go to Texas in a covered wagon
He pulled out his fiddle and he [A]rosined up his bow
And he [G]played a little tune down a new cut road